==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English noun '''coppeweb''', ''spider web'', from Old English '''āttercoppe''', ''spider'', from '''ātor''' (''poison'') and '''copp''' (''head'').

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''cobweb''', plural '''cobwebs'''
# a [[spider]]'s [[web]], or the [[remain]]s of one
# one of its [[filament]]s; [[gossamer]]
# an [[intricate]] [[plot]]
#{{computing}} a [[web page]] that either has not been [[updated]] for a long time, or that is rarely [[visited]]

